  <td bgcolor="#29496B">
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="White" size="3"><b>HELP
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>
<p>
<table border="0" width="100%">
 <tr>
  <td><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="3"><b>MAIN SETTINGS</b>
  <hr noshade size="1" width="100%"></td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h1"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Track URL</b></font></td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This is the URL where you have placed the track directory.  The track URL should end with /track/track.cfm (e.g. http://www.e-zonemedia.com/track/track.cfm)
  </td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h2"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Datasource</b></font></td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   The datasource that you have created for fuseAds.
  </td>
 </tr>
   <tr>
  <td><a name="h2a"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Database Type </b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This select box allows you to select what type of database you are using. You have four choices, MSSQL, ACCESS, MYSQL, ORACLE.
   If you use Oracle, please make sure you use the ODBC driver and NOT the native driver.
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h3"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Administrator Password</b></font></td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   Password for the adminsitrator.
  </td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="3"><b>BANNERS</b>
  <hr noshade size="1" width="100%"></td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h4"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Client</b></font></td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   The client the banner belongs to.  Banners have to belong to clients.
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Banner Type</b></font></td>
 </tr>
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This option defines if the banner is located locally or externally.  External banners require you to fill out a text box with your ad code, and local ad require you to fill out the image URL and Re-direct URL.
   
   NOTE: External ads can be HTML, DHTML, or Javascript.
  </td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h5"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Banner Size</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This is the size of your banner.  Width x Height
  </td>
 </tr>

 <tr>
  <td> <a name="h6"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Category</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This is the category the banner belongs to.  A banner can belong to multiple categories.
  </td>
 </tr> 
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h7"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Description</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This is the description of the banner.  The description is only for administrative puporses and will not be displayed along with the local banners.
  </td>
 </tr> 
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h8"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Track Impressions</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This option lets you decided if you want to track impressions for the banner you are inserting/updating.
  </td>
 </tr> 
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h9"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Maximum Impressions</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   The maximum impressions a banner can have.  This is useful for a campaign that you have to sell x amount of impressions.  (e.g. If you put 10000, a banner will not be displayed after 10000 impressions).  If you leave it blank or put 0, the banner impressions are unlimited.
  </td>
 </tr> 
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h10"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Track Click Throughs</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This option lets you decided if you want to track clicks on the banner you are inserting/updating.
  </td>
 </tr> 
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h11"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Maximum Clicks</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   The maximum clicks a banner can have.  This is useful for a campaign that you have to sell x amount of click throughs for.  (e.g. If you put 10000, a banner will not be displayed after 10000 click throughs).  If you leave it blank or put 0, the banner click throughs are unlimited.
  </td>
 </tr> 
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h12"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Start Date</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   The date the banner starts to display.  If you leave the date blank the banner will start to appear after it is inserted.
  </td>
 </tr> 
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h13"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>End Date</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   The date the banner stops displaying.  If you leave the date blank the banner will never end.
  </td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h14"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Do not run on</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This option lets you specify days you don't want the banner to be displayed. (e.g. if you click on Tuesday the banner will never appear on Tuesdays).
  </td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h15"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Start at</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This option lets you specify when the banner starts being displayed during a 1 day period.  (e.g. If you select 7:00:00, the banner will only be displayed after 7AM)
  </td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h16"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>To:</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This option lets you specify when you want the banner to stop being displayed during a 1 day period.  (e.g. If you select 20:59:59, the banner will stop being displayd at 9PM)
  </td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h17"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Image URL</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This field is only required when Local banner type is specified.  It is the URL of your banner. (e.g. http://www.e-zonemedia.com/banner/mybanner.gif)
  </td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h18"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>Re-directURL</b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This field is only required when Local banner type is specified.  It is the URL that the user will be re-directed to after they have clicked on the banner.
  </td>
 </tr>
 
 <tr>
  <td><a name="h19"><font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2"><b>External banner code </b></font></td>
 </tr> 
 <tr>
  <td>
   <font face="Tahoma,Arial" color="Black" size="2">
   This field is only required when External banner type is specified.  External ads can be HTML, DHTML, or Javascript.
   
   <b>NOTE</b>: If you need to need a random number for your external tag, you can insert <b>#RandNumber#</b> (make sure you include the pound symbols) where you want the random number to appear.  fuseAds will take care of replacing #RandNumber# with a random number between 100,000 and 999,999.
   The reason you might need to include this number is for cache busting techniques. Your ad company who gives you your tags, will probably inform you of this. It is
   mostly commonly used when displaying multiple copies of the same tag on one page.
  </td>
 </tr>

</table>

